    "client_msg_id": "eaa91fd7-ae78-4d67-86ca-3ad99f53071c",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "I finally had occasion to try out Obsidian today. Some notes after 5 minutes of use.\n\n• The initial experience is a blank screen without bullets. I thought the outliner view was the #1 selling point of such tools? Do people use Obsidian to write free-form text?\n• I can copy a set of nested bullets from Obsidian to LogSeq and it works great. In the other direction, though, Obsidian loses all the nested structure I copied from LogSeq.\nOverall the experience has been surprising. The open source clone felt like a more polished onboarding experience than the relatively proprietary and centrally coordinated product. I'm curious if that matches other people's experience.",
    "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
    "ts": "1686335727.605889",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "CqV",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I finally had occasion to try out Obsidian today. Some notes after 5 minutes of use.\n\n"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_list",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "rich_text_section",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "The initial experience is a blank screen without bullets. I thought the outliner view was the #1 selling point of such tools? Do people use Obsidian to write free-form text?"
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "rich_text_section",
                "elements": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "I can copy a set of nested bullets from Obsidian to LogSeq and it works great. In the other direction, though, Obsidian loses all the nested structure I copied from LogSeq."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ],
            "style": "bullet",
            "indent": 0,
            "border": 0
          },
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "\nOverall the experience has been surprising. The open source clone felt like a more polished onboarding experience than the relatively proprietary and centrally coordinated product. I'm curious if that matches other people's experience."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
