    "client_msg_id": "e3943e73-2e2a-4ce5-a870-16163e3377b9",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Meta commentary:\n\nA marketing firm emailed me about doing a quid pro quo where I'd promote this event on social media, in our newsletter, banners on our website, etc, and then they'd give us some free passes.\n\nMy typical reply to these sorts of things is a flat \"No\" or simply the ol' _Report Spam_, but… this is GDC. So there are some people here who might actually be interested.\n\nSo instead I replied \"none of those [forms of promotion] would work\", and they just sent me the codes anyway.\n\nYes, mentioning it here means they are getting a bit of promotion they otherwise wouldn't get. But if anyone is actually interested in \"attending\" this virtual event, I figure it's worth saving them $150.",
    "user": "UC2A2ARPT",
    "ts": "1686347505.631999",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "ajh",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Meta commentary:\n\nA marketing firm emailed me about doing a quid pro quo where I'd promote this event on social media, in our newsletter, banners on our website, etc, and then they'd give us some free passes.\n\nMy typical reply to these sorts of things is a flat \"No\" or simply the ol' "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Report Spam",
                "style": {
                  "italic": true
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ", but… this is GDC. So there are some people here who might actually be interested.\n\nSo instead I replied \"none of those [forms of promotion] would work\", and they just sent me the codes anyway.\n\nYes, mentioning it here means they are getting a bit of promotion they otherwise wouldn't get. But if anyone is actually interested in \"attending\" this virtual event, I figure it's worth saving them $150."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
